The paper deals with statistical data privacy and the use of linear reconstruction attacks, which are commonly studied in the field of cryptography and computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of data structures and algorithms for solving nonlinear formulations, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of M-estimators and empirical risk minimization algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of distributional assumptions on the data, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the release of statistics about sensitive attributes and their relation to nonsensitive attributes, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
